{
  "texts": [
    "One table contains data that has been subjected to data augmentation techniques, which involves artificially generating new data by making changes to existing data samples.",
    "The other table contains data that has not undergone any data augmentation.",
    "Both tables are likely used to compare the performance of machine learning or other data-driven models on the augmented versus nonaugmented data.Data augmentation is a technique where new training samples are generated by applying transformations such as rotations, flips, and scaling to the original images.",
    "This can increase the diversity of the training data and improve the performance of the model.",
    "The third table in the analysis described the class-wise prediction performance of the top three best-performing models."
  ]
}